{"word":"ἑτέρωθι","slug":"ἑτέρωθι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἑτέρωθι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἕτερος'><el>ἕτερος</el></a>\n<p/><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>on the other side</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:ἄλλοθι'><el>ἄλλοθι</el></a>, <i>elsewhere</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἑτ. τοῦ λόγου</el> <i>in another part</i> of my story, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>at another time</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}